## Linux Networking

The command `ifcongig` is used to display all the networking interface configured on any Linux system. This command details both IPV4 and IPV6 IP address, all the details of the packets transmitted and received, any erors oocured while Tx/Rx packets, etc.  

```bash
âœ— ifconfig
